{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa1fb01d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3375"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3375"},"text":"§ 3375.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Undefinitized contractual actions: time limit","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No undefinitized contractual action may extend beyond 90 days without a written determination by the Secretary of the military department concerned, the head of the Defense Agency concerned, the commander of the combatant command concerned, or the Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition and Sustainment (as applicable) that it is in the best interests of the military department, the Defense Agency, the combatant command, or the Department of Defense, respectively, to continue the action.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa1fb01e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1819/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1819(a)","children":[],"tail":", (f), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4189"},"text":"134 Stat. 4189","children":[],"tail":", 4190.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa1fb01f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa1fb020-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idaa1fb021-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"tex